node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Alan Stokes on September 19, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, child and indoor.

node.text:
I have never been in so much pain and sadness in my entire life. All I feel is darkness like the whole world has collapsed on my chest and I fight every day to live on with this void and emptiness..I cared and loved you more than anyone in my life and now I have lost my father-figure. You were the strongest, most thoughtful, and kindest soul. 

外公, I adored and admired you and looked up to you so much and worked my ass off to try to give you a better life as you once did for me and Alex, but I never got to give you the life you deserved.. Because of that, I have so much anger and regret. You brought so so so much joy in my life and I can not even express how much agony is in my life now that I’ve lost you. 

I never thought this day would come so soon and I wish I got another chance to tell you how much I love you and to hug you one final time because i would never let go..
I prayed for you every day and night that God would protect you and watch over you.. and now, I pray that God softened your heart in your final moments and you accepted him into your life..

You mean more to me than life itself and I regret I never got a chance to tell you this one final time to your face. 
Not a day will go by that I won’t think about you.. I will forever remember the man you are by trying to follow your footsteps. 
I hope to see you again one day and give you that hug. 

Rest In Peace Sweet Soul ❤️
1943-2021
